				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I would like to mention the "power" of a SMN/WHM . This may stir up some controversy, but SMN/WHM pretty much steals the job of a WHM in the PT post 50. I've had the luxury of grouping with a SMN/WHM for a loooong time, and I only miss 2 things about WHMs thus far... Raise II and Protectra III (I hate having to Protect III 6 times). 
<br />

<br />
Now, Raise II (and III) is a big loss, but if you don't die often, then its no big deal really... and if you do, there may be a nice WHM willing to Raise II you anyway.  
<br />

<br />
There are a few other things missing as well... pre66 there is no Viruna exactly... but Leviathan's Spring Water would do the trick. And @ 64 (I think), SMN/WHM gets Erase. 
<br />

<br />
It really is "to each his own" but I've found that a SMN/WHM (with or without Fenrir) really fills in for the WHM job... and still has the MP to do group Haste/Blink/Stoneskin/Enthunder(good against fishies!). 
<br />

<br />
Now... if one day the level cap gets raised to the point where ???/RDM gives Refresh and Convert... I think that will make things VERY different.  But, if SE ever did that, they would nerf the ability in some way, like they did ???/SAM.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
